 Omah Lay And Tems Release From Police Custody in Uganda Omah Lay and Tems have been reportedly released from police custody in Uganda.  The two musicians were arrested over the weekend for flouting COVID-19 guidelines in Uganda. This is after they performed at a concert in the country’s city, Kampala. However, after calls on social media for their release, they have been set free by the police. Mr Eazi broke the news on Twitter. Pleased  to hear that My brothers and sisters are to be released &  the case is resolved, Big love to everyone who worked on this & Special thanks to @adoniaayebare & The Government of Uganda, Chief Of Justice In Uganda ??. African relations must keep fostering strong! — Uncle Njobvu (@mreazi) December 15, 2020